Sentencas: Pr0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-delta(PSCF) and Gd0.2Ce0.8O2-delta(GDC) powders were synthesized by a citric acid-nitrates self-propagating combustion method, and La0.9Sr0.1Ga0.8Mg0.2O3-delta (LSGM) electrolyte powder was prepared by conventional solid state reaction process.
Titulo: Improved Performance of Symmetrical Solid Oxide Fuel Cells with Redox-reversible Pr0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ Electrodes

Titulo: Improved Performance of Symmetrical Solid Oxide Fuel Cells with Redox-reversible Pr0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ Electrodes

Titulo: Improved Performance of Symmetrical Solid Oxide Fuel Cells with Redox-reversible Pr0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ Electrodes

Sentencas: The phase structure, chemical compatibility, polarization resistance, cross-section microstructure and the cell performance were investigated by X-ray diffraction (XRD), electrochemical impedance spectra, scanning electron microscope (SEM) and self-assembly SOFC test system, respectively.
Titulo: Improved Performance of Symmetrical Solid Oxide Fuel Cells with Redox-reversible Pr0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ Electrodes

Sentencas: The results indicate that PSCF powder exhibits a single perovskite with cubic symmetry and a good redox reversibility.
Titulo: Improved Performance of Symmetrical Solid Oxide Fuel Cells with Redox-reversible Pr0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ Electrodes

Sentencas: The GDC function layer dramatically improve the chemical compatibility among PSCF, LSGM in hydrogen and the cell performance.
Titulo: Improved Performance of Symmetrical Solid Oxide Fuel Cells with Redox-reversible Pr0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ Electrodes

Sentencas: The area specific resistance (ASR) of PSCF I GDC decreased from 6.892 Omega.cm(2) to 0.314 Omega.cm(2) in hydrogen at 800 degrees C and the maximum power density increased from 269 mW/cm(2) to 463 mW/cm(2) using humidified hydrogen (3%H20) as fuel and ambient air as oxidant.
Titulo: Improved Performance of Symmetrical Solid Oxide Fuel Cells with Redox-reversible Pr0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ Electrodes

Sentencas: The results indicate that PSCF is a promising electrode material for symmetrical solid oxide fuel cells, and GDC function layer is a potential way to enhance the long-term stability.
Titulo: Improved Performance of Symmetrical Solid Oxide Fuel Cells with Redox-reversible Pr0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ Electrodes
